--- In nbwrpg@y..., "Soulstice Omega" <thecode@p...> wrote:
> Squawktalk, listening to Megatron, flies to Cepta.
> 
> Squawktalk: Hello, hello, you want the tour, right? Of course you 
do! Okay! Anyway, first of all, this is the main chamber, it serves 
well because it's main. It's where you are when you first walk in, 
it's where you are when you see the door! It's where we go sometime 
to leave the base, it's also where we go after we come in! It's got 
all these cool computers and stuff, and tables and that and it's 
where we are right now! Isn't that a coincidence? Well, anyway, it's 
a nice room maybe a little too dusty but then again maybe not and 
it's a good room because it has lots of room, and it leads into all 
of the other rooms, it's also one of the biggest rooms, which is 
good, because everyone might try to come in at the same time, and if 
they do and the room is really tiny then everyone will be crowded and 
the base might explode. Also, it's big because something might happen 
like someone breaks in, and there might be a shootout and everyone 
will get shot if there isn't much room, did I mention that? I don't 
think I did, correct me if I'm wrong, but I know I'm not wrong 
because I'm right. Anyway, I'm Squawktalk and you are? I mean what's 
your name, I'm not calling you Squawktalk, that would be silly, 
wouldn't it? I hope you have a nice name, you probably do, but I 
still hope, because hoping can get you stuff sometimes, and anyway, 
it's fun, so about your name, it should be nice because my name is 
cool and I met you, didn't I? Anyhow, what I was trying to say is 
that maybe we've spent too long in this room, want to go to the next 
room? It would be good because then we won't be in this room and 
we'll be in the next one instead and I can talk to you in there just 
hurry up and don't take forever, okay?...
